Prime Minister Antonis Samaras of the Hellenic Republic will be visiting the White House on August 8, 2013. The visit aims to highlight the strong relationship between the U.S. and Greece, as well as the ongoing support for Greece's efforts to reform its economy. President Obama and Prime Minister Samaras will discuss various topics, including defense cooperation, trade partnership, regional cooperation, counterterrorism efforts, the Cyprus settlement, and developments in North Africa and Syria.